<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7623677-pam-k">Pam K</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I was initially surprised, too, but really liked this complexity in Neni. Neni had compassion for Cindy, but despite her understanding of the reasons <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I was initially surprised, too, but really liked this complexity in Neni. Neni had compassion for Cindy, but despite her understanding of the reasons for her issues, I thought she was also perplexed by Cindy's choices, given all she had? Also, Neni is clearly a survivor, and very pragmatic. Lastly, I thought it had something to do with her traditional views of men and women, and that Clark (&amp; not his wife), would be the one to support, for their own survival. Interesting how wrong they both were....<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
